 # Use isTrue and isFalse matchers

When writing tests, prefer using `isTrue` and `isFalse` matchers instead of `equals(true)` or `equals(false)`.

## ❌ Don't

```dart
expect(value, equals(true));
expect(value, equals(false));
```

```dart
expect(value, true);
expect(value, false);
```

## ✅ Do

```dart
expect(value, isTrue);
expect(value, isFalse);
```

# Do not use equals

For better readablity, do not use equals.

## ❌ Don't

```dart
expect(value, equals('my value'));
```

## ✅ Do

```dart
expect(value, 'my value');
```